                             Wing Commander

Sign On:

After loading the credits play until your press a key.
Some or all of these options will appear.

o Start Vega Camp
  Select to begin your first game, or to create new character or camp.
o Continue Camp.
  Select if you have already played and wish to continue a saved char.
o Start Secret Missions
  Select if you have installed the "Secret Missions" disk and wish to
  begin the Secret Mission Camp.

In the Bar:

o Talking to people
  Move the pointer to the character you want to talk to.  When the green
  cross hairs appear, press select to learn what they have to say.  Press
  any key to advance the conversation.
o The Pilots Chalkboard
  Displays each pilots record, move the pointer over the blackboard and
  press select, click again to return to the main view.
o Fly the training Simulator
  Select the training Sim. move the pointer over the ship you want to
  fight against and press select to begin.  The less time you take to
  destroy the enemy ship the higher your score.  Press ESC to end
  sim.
o Enter Barracks
  Select the door on the right to enter the Barracks
  (alot more docs then I want to type at the moment)

General Command Summary:

A - Engage Autopilot
C - Select Communications Panel/Clear Incoming COMM
D - Display Ship Damage
CTRL-E Eject From Ship (Looser)
G - Select Ships Gun Type
L - Lock Target Computer
M - Change Message Duration
CTRL-M Toggle Music On / Off (I don't have a speaker!)
N - (Press Once), Select Navigation
    (Press Twice), View Navigation Screen
P - Pause Game
CTRL-S Sound On and Off (In SPACE only)
T - Select Targeting Computer/Active Target
V - COMM Video ON/OFF
W - Select Missle Type
ALT-X Exit to DOS
ESC (Leave COMM Mode or NAVIGATION MAP)

Switching Camera Views:

F1 - View Front
F2 - View Left
F3 - View Right
F4 - View Rear
F5 - Chase Plane View
F6 - Battle View
F7 - Tatical View
F8 - Missle Camera View (Neato)
F9 - Tailing View

Keyboard Flight Controls:

Numeric Keypad (Steer Ship)
+ (Increase Speed)
- (Decrease Speed)
< or , or INS (Rotate Ship Left)
> or . or DEL (Rotate Ship Right)
TAB or * (Fire Afterburners)
SPACEBAR (Fire Selected Gun)
ENTER (Fire Missles/Mines)

Typed by Jenetic Bytemare and Chuckles
